        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 5:24PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Batesville, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pope, Courtland, Sardis, Eureka Springs, and Batesville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
